        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:6:24:2",
        "text": [
          " لَا تَأْكُلْ بِالْيَسَارِ وَ أَنْتَ تَسْتَطِيعُ ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.hubeali": [
            "Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Al Husayn, from Al Qasim Bin Muhammad, from Ali Bin Abu Hamza, from Abu Baseer, ",
            "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Do not eat with the left hand and you are able (to eat with the right)’."
          ],
          "en.sarwar": [
            "2. Ahmad ibn Muhammad has narrated from al-Husayn, from al-Qasim ibn Muhammad from Ali ibn abu Hamzah from abu Basir who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘Do not eat with your left hand if you can.’” "
          ]
        }
